sql.sqlStatement:
Create a border around the overall graph. 
The 'pack' attribute specifies the size, in points, of a margin around each part (72 points = 1 inch).

SELECT 
  '{'                            as [Item], 
  'United States of America'     as [Label], 
  'United States of America'     as [Tooltip], 
  'Border 0 Begin'               as [style name], 
  'pack="12" packmode=array_ut2' as [attributes]

SELECT 
  [State Code]                      as [item],       
  'Medium Square'                   as [style name],
  'sortv=%rsc%'                     as [attributes],
  [State]                           as [label],
  5                                 as [split length],
  '\l'                              as [line ending], 
  [State Code]                      as [external label],
  [State]                           as [tooltip],
  [Region]                          as [cluster],
  'Border 6 '                       as [cluster style name],
  [Region]                          as [cluster tooltip],
  'sortv=%clc% packmode=array_utr3' as [cluster attributes],
  [Division]                        as [subcluster],
  'Border %scc% '                   as [subcluster style name],
  [Division]                        as [subcluster tooltip],
  'sortv=%scc% packmode=array_utr3' as [subcluster attributes]
FROM 
  [census regions$] 
ORDER BY 
  [Region]     ASC, 
  [Division]   ASC, 
  [State Code] ASC

SELECT 
  [StateCode]                               as [Item],
  [StateCode] & ' to ' &[NeighborStateCode] as [TOOLTIP],   
  [NeighborStateCode]                       as [Related Item],
  'Flow'                                    as [Style Name]
FROM 
  [neighbor state$]

SELECT 
  [NeighborStateCode]                       as [Item],
  [NeighborStateCode] & ' to ' &[StateCode] as [TOOLTIP],   
  [StateCode]                               as [Related Item],
  'Flow'                                    as [Style Name]
FROM 
  [neighbor state$]
Publish the graph as a file
PUBLISH ALL VIEWS AS DIRECTED GRAPH example01-all-views-directed
PUBLISH ALL VIEWS AS UNDIRECTED GRAPH example01-all-views-undirected

SELECT 
  [State Code]          as [Item],       
  [State Code]          as [Label],
  [State]               as [External Label],
  'Medium Square'       as [style name],
  [Region]              as [cluster],
  'Border 2 '           as [cluster style name],
  [Division]            as [subcluster],
  'Border 4 '           as [subcluster style name]
FROM 
  [census regions$] 
ORDER BY 
  [Region]     ASC, 
  [Division]   ASC, 
  [State Code] ASC

SELECT 
  [State Code]          as [Item],       
  [State Code]          as [Label],
  [Division]            as [subcluster],
  'Border 6 '           as [subcluster style name],
  'Medium Square'       as [style name]
FROM 
  [census regions$] 
ORDER BY 
  [Division]   ASC

SELECT 
  [State Code]                      as [Item],       
  'Medium Square'                   as [style name],
  'sortv=%rsc%'                     as [attributes],
  [State Code]                      as [Label],
  [State]                           as [External Label],
  [State]                           as [Tooltip],
  [Region]                          as [cluster],
  'Border 4 '                       as [cluster style name],
  [Region]                          as [cluster tooltip],
  'sortv=%clc% packmode=array_utr3' as [cluster attributes] 
FROM 
  [census regions$] 
ORDER BY 
  [Region]     ASC, 
  [State Code] ASC

SELECT 
  [State Code]          as [Item],       
  'Medium Square'       as [style name],
  'sortv=%rsc%'         as [attributes],
  [State Code]          as [Label],
  [State]               as [External Label],
  [State]               as [Tooltip]
FROM 
  [census regions$] 
ORDER BY 
  [State Code] ASC

buttons.superTip: The table gives the name of the attribute, the graph components (node, edge, etc.) which use the attribute and the type of the attribute (strings representing legal values of that type). Where applicable, the table also gives a default value for the attribute, a minimum allowed setting for numeric attributes, and certain restrictions on the use of the attribute.
